description: From Middle English bewenden, biwenden, from Old English bewendan (“to turn around”), from Proto-Germanic *biwandijaną. Equivalent to be- +‎ wend.

verbs.description: bewend (third-person singular simple present bewends, present participle bewending, simple past and past participle bewent or bewended)

entries.meaning: (transitive, chiefly dialectal) To turn; turn around.
